TY  - JOUR
AU  - Matveyev, Egor
AU  - Zhdanov, Alexei
T1  - Optimal Capital Structure with Imperfect Competition
PY  - 2022
Y1  - 2022/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/rcfs/cfac001
JO  - The Review of Corporate Finance Studies
JA  - Review of Corporate Finance Studies
VL  - 11
IS  - 2
SP  - 314
EP  - 363
SN  - 2046-9128
AB  - We develop a model of optimal capital structure in imperfectly competitive markets by focusing on a duopoly. The model endogenizes both the financing and investment decisions of firms. We show that in equilibrium the industry leader uses debt conservatively, while the follower uses debt more aggressively and, as the result, defaults first. The model generates novel predictions about the leverage choices of the leader and the follower, their default likelihood, and the degree of leverage dispersion between competing firms. These predictions are strongly supported by the data. (JEL G13, G34, L13)
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rcfs/cfac001
ER  - 



